# 7. 世界に響く歌声を

Ichika: Yeah, I should use this sound here. There isn't a huge difference, but I feel like it's more reflective of the kindness I'm trying to capture.
Ichika: That just leaves the key change between the bridge and the last chorus...
Ichika: Okay, the bridge should be all set now.
Ichika: Come to think of it... I had to think a lot about what sorts of phrases I wanted to use for the bridge.
Ichika: But I'm glad that I did. You only get to hear the bridge once, so it has a fairly different kind of presence compared to the chorus, which is played several times.
Ichika: I wrote it with everyone smiling in mind. As brief as this phrase is, I wanted it to become this unforgettable glimmer.
Ichika: That's why I won't use any effects. I want to use just raw sound. Next is...
Ichika: Okay, let's see how this sounds...
Ichika's Song: ♪————
Ichika: *Gasp* This song... It's even better than I...!
Ichika: B-But I shouldn't be patting myself on the back just yet. I need to hear how it sounds when Miku sings it...
Ichika: Ready, Miku...?
Miku: ♪————
Ichika: ...!
Miku: ♪————
Ichika: (This is incredible...)
Ichika: (I-If I showed this to Miku, she'd probably...)
Ichika: She has to hear this...
Ichika: Miku needs to listen to this song...!
Miku: Hmm... I'm playing pretty well today... It might be nice to jam with someone else...
Ichika: Miku, are you there?!
Miku: W-Wah! You scared me...!
Miku: What's wrong? You seem really flustered... You also seem really happy, though...
Ichika: That's because I am... The truth is, I've been working on my own song...
Miku: Your own song?
Ichika: Yeah, I worked really hard on it... And finally, today... I'm finally finished writing it. Which is why...
Ichika: Please, Miku... I want you to listen to it....!
Miku: Of course. I'd love to hear your song, Ichika.
Ichika: H-How was it...?
Miku: Amazing...
Miku: You've created a wonderful song. It's clear that you put an incredible amount of thought into it...
Ichika: You can tell...?!
Miku: Yes. Each note gently showed me just how much you care about the others, how you want to be there for them and cherish their brilliant smiles.
Miku: Not only that, you chose the instruments that Leo/need uses. You must have had the others in mind while writing it.
Ichika: Oh...
Ichika: That's right... I wrote this hoping that we'd play it as a band.
Ichika: At the moment, only Honami knows that I'm writing a song...
Ichika: But now that you've given me your seal of approval, Miku, I think I can present it to the others as our newest song.
Miku: I see. That means...
Miku: This song is going to let me sing with all of you in your world.
Ichika: Miku...
Miku: Obviously, I'm not the same Miku that's in your world... However, while listening to this song, I got the feeling that it connects me to all of you girls.
Ichika: (Oh...)
Ichika: I felt that too...
Ichika: I thought really hard, trying a lot of different melodies and having you sing them...
Ichika: At first, I felt so happy just to hear you sing phrases that I'd come up with, Miku...
Ichika: But after a while, I began to feel bad about having you sing all these incomplete melodies.
Miku: Ichika...
Ichika: But I was able to approach the sound I was going for with the help of a certain someone. I was able to produce a melody that I feel satisfied with because of them.
Ichika: And... Miku, when I heard you sing that melody for the first time, I...
Ichika: I thought our hearts were in perfect sync.
Ichika: The way I wanted to show how much I want to be there for everyone and how brilliant their smiles are... Miku, through your singing voice, you said that you understand.
Ichika: That made me so happy. Which is why when I finished writing my song earlier...
Ichika: It felt like we made it together... I didn't create it alone. This song felt like our song.
Miku: Yes... I have to think that my counterpart also feels the same way.
Miku: I mean, she sounded like she was having so much fun while singing your song, Ichika.
Ichika: Miku...
Miku: I also want lots and lots of people in your world to hear the song you and her created, Ichika...
Miku: This song, your thoughts, your feelings, this melody... The people who need it most are going to be so touched by them all.
Ichika: Yeah... I hope so too.
Miku: Um, Ichika...? Would you mind if I tried singing it?
Ichika: Huh...?
Miku: I want to sing your song, too.
Ichika: *Gasp*
Ichika: Then, can I... Can I sing with you?
Miku: Did you think I was going to say no?
Miku: Let's sing!
Miku: ♪————
Ichika: Okay, here I go...
Ichika: ♪————
Miku: ♪————
Ichika: (...!)
Ichika: (Our voices are becoming one...)
Ichika & Miku: ♪————
Ichika: (This is so much fun...!)
Ichika: (I wrote this song with Miku, and now we're really singing it together...)
Ichika: (This is the closest I've ever felt to Miku.)
Ichika: (Music really is a wonderful thing... Not only does it have the power to resonate in someone's heart, it has the ability to tie people's hearts together...)
Ichika: (I want to keep writing more songs... With Miku.)
Ichika: (Songs that really move people's hearts.)
Ichika & Miku: ♪————
